  "body": "<!--ðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’Ž\r\n\r\nHellooo! ðŸ˜„ \r\n\r\nTo help us tend to your issue faster, please search our currently open issues before submitting a new one.\r\nExisting issues often contain information about workarounds, resolution, or progress updates.\r\n\r\nðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’Ž-->\r\n\r\n# ðŸ’Ž Issue\r\n\r\n### Background\r\n\r\nCurrently, we do not allow for short slot duration testnets due to some bad math in our beacon nodes. The lowest we can go is 4 seconds per slot as we have some logic scattered throughout that performs operations twice or four times per slot, and if we divide uint64(1) / 4 currently, we will not obtain the same result.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nA PR to resolve this issue will find all uses of params.BeaconConfig().SecondsPerSlot and ensure all logic works the same even if that value is set to 1 second per slot.",
